  "articleSummary": "This technical tutorial provides performance optimization strategies for AngularJS v1.x developers struggling with application bloat and digest cycle overhead. The author argues against the \"over-AngularJSification\" of apps, specifically targeting the overuse of two-way data binding, excessive `$scope` inheritance, and deep directive nesting. Key recommendations include adopting one-way binding, utilizing Browserify for dependency management, and offloading complex UI fragments to native JS factories or alternative libraries like ReactJS. The tone is informal and pragmatic, employing metaphors of physical exhaustion and \"hammer-and-nail\" over-engineering to advocate for leaner, more framework-agnostic architectural patterns.",
